inn1.comm: back of a length on off stump, Cook opens the face and gets it fine of backward point
touch of movement for Lee, this is outside off and shapes away from Bell who shoulders arms
makes him play this time, fuller on off stump and it's defended square into the off side
beauty! This one beats the edge, it was shorter and seamed away from Bell...it was still on the rise when Wade gathered it
onto the front foot, pushes into the off side and there's a gap at cover
squares him up a touch on off stump but it is defended solidly to point...a testing first over from Lee
quite a big appeal from McKay as this takes the pad and glances away fine past the keeper but it didn't seem to have much going for it
wide outside off and left alone
that's a good length, full on off stump and it squirts off a thick outside edge as Bell pushes into the shot
punchy stroke from Bell, driven firmly back towards the bowler who gets his left hand on it
back of a length outside off, left alone and this one barely reaches Matthew Wade
good one to finish with, shapes away from off stump and scoots past the outside edge...this is a morning where a Test-match top-order could serve England well
outside off, going across Cook, and left alone
short run from Lee, on off stump and defended to the off side
back of his full run now, on off stump and Cook defends from the back foot to cover
a cracker! Moves away from Cook and beats the outside edge as he is drawn into pushing away from his body
fuller this time, Cook gets a decent stride in and blocks firmly to the off side
outside off and left alone...a maiden either side of that brief stoppage
full outside off and left alone
seams back into Bell but it is wide enough for him to leave alone
out with a hit! Bell was short. He pushed it towards Cummins at mid-on and raced off for a single after a series of dot balls.
back of a length, no width for Cook as he plays it back to the bowler
worked off the stumps through square leg
loose from Bell, he fishes outside off without any footwork and is lucky not to edge this to the keeper
another tight single as Cook works this towards midwicket but this time it's safe enough
movement for Lee but Bell plays this one well with soft hands and guides it fine of backward point towards third man
well bowled, pushed up very full to Cook who drives with his feet caught in the crease and gets beaten
first hint of width to Cook to cuts it firmly but David Warner pulls off a brilliant piece of work at backward point to prevent a boundary
back on off stump, Bell walks into a defensive push to cover
this one jags back onto Bell and plays it late and the ball bobbles towards the slips
opens the face and places this nicely into the covers

Given caught behind! Bell reviews straight away. Has this taken the inside edge? Was a superb delivery that nipped back and it appears it may have hit his trouser pocket. Now the players have walked off for rain and still no decision given. Everyone hanging around. And it's not out. So Bell walks off but isn't out.
moves back into Bell who works it neatly down to fine leg
edged! Cook goes for the cut and it flies just over David Hussey at second slip then Lee pulls off a good diving save a third man
back defending as he plays into the off side
full outside off and left alone
starts full on off stump and driven without much timing into the covers
back of a length outside off and left alone
tucked off the body into the leg side
back of a length, Bell goes for the pull and gets a big top edge that flies over the keeper and slips for the first boundary off the bat
lovely drive, leans onto the front and punches perfectly straight back down the pitch...Doherty chases hard and pulls it in just before the rope. Outfield still quite damp.
pushed across outside off and left alone...Cummins finding his feet in that first over but the speeds are good
full on off stump, sweetly timed drive but he picks out the man at cover
dragged short and wide outside off, Bell chases it and loses his shape on the shot...it's too wide for the umpire
flies off a thick outside edge as Bell drives, it goes in the air for a while but wide of backward point
solid this time from Bell, comes forward and defends with bat and pad together
back of a length and played to the covers
that's a good one, angled into Bell then straightens off the seam...actually beats the edge by quite a distance
fraction to wide this time and Bell pulls his bat inside the line
back of a length, not quite as full as Lee was, and Cook nudges into the leg side
fuller on off stump and defended with a solid thud to cover
the speed gun edging towards 90mph as Cook again pushes into the off side
dropped in short and it's quick, Cook goes for the hook and is fortunate that the top edge doesn't carry to fine leg
back of a length outside off, shapes back into the right hander but he's able to leave
opens the face and runs it down to third man
comes towards the bowler who drops it shorter and Bell then pulls through midwicket although doesn't time it cleanly
short of a length, defended to the off side
now he opens up through the off side, it was a full delivery and he didn't hold back with a drive which flew in the air but between cover and mid-off
what a gem of a shot. A perfect on-drive from Bell as he leans on a full ball with pristine timing. Even on a damp outfield it raced away
drags the length back and Bell defends
beaten as he tries to drive. McKay answers back a touch with that last ball as it swings away nicely to beat the edge
worked towards midwicket
offered some width and latches into a cut but picks out backward point
lovely from Cook now, full outside off and he drives it square through the off side picking the gap perfectly. His first boundary.
short ball this time and Cook plays a swivel-pull all along the ground through square leg
a slower delivery which is quite short, Bell runs it down to third man
another slower ball to end the over and Cook pushes to the off side
round the wicket, very full and driven down to long-off
stays round the wicket to Cook who pushes easily down to long-on
easily milked down to long-off passed a diving Doherty
beaten as he tries to cut
comes forward and works from off stump to square leg
sweeps firmly from quite wide outside off, connects well but square leg makes a good save
length ball, dabbed towards point
pitched up on the stumps and whipped smartly in front of midwicket for another sweetly timed boundary for Bell
length ball outside off, dropped short on the off side for a quick single
good length, sliding across Cook and leaving him a touch, draws a false stroke - but no edge
short and slightly wide, slashed behind point with a workmanlike swing of the arms
tight line on off, good length, defended into off side
tossed up and swept to deep backward square
flighted on the stumps, pushed into the off side coming forward
full toss from Doherty and Bell had already reversed the grip, reverse paddling four through the vacant third man area - impudent stuff
tossed up and driven to cover
length ball on off, tapped short of cover for another one
short and wide, Cook hangs back and slaps this behind point for four more - all looking a lot easier for the English opening pair now
full and outside off, driven to mid-off on the front foot
tight line, quite full in length again, punched towards cover
back of a length, Bell thinks about pulling but decides against it, ducking his head out of the way
short of a good length again, on the stumps, defended back down the track and Lee fields
full and wide, steered through point to the man on the boundary rope
short, on the body, nudged into the leg side
good length, on the line of off, pushed defensively to cover
pitched up outside off, Cook shuffles across and drives to mid-off, who misfields and they pick up one
touch short, on the stumps, defended
bit of width and chopped through gully, third man comes round to cut it off
in the corridor outside off, driven through cover
pitched up on leg stump, clipped through square
full, almost yorker length, and Cook does well to dig it out in front of middle and off
pitched up and driven into the covers
length ball on off, driven through mid-off and George Bailey misfields in Australian-middle-order-sitcom fashion to send the ball skittering away for four
defended in front of the stumps
wide of the stumps and cut aerially through the gully region

oh no, Bell MK II suffers a familiar glitch, hit in front of off and he has to go, no matter how attractive his 41 was! It was another testing ball from Lee, nipping back just a shade and Bell tried to drive back down the pitch, looked like a good call from Aleem Dar and the batsman decides against reviewing
almost two in two! Length ball down the leg side and Cook gets a faint edge on it, the ball hitting Wade's fingertips and running away
defended in front of the stumps
tight line and length, forward defensive
too wide this time and Cook hammers a cut shot to the rope, a familiar, thrashing blow
length ball outside off, no stroke
pushed through outside off, edged on to the pads and they nab one
pitched up on the legs, clipped through square
back of a length outside off, played towards point
length ball, seaming back a touch from outside off and deflected past leg stump via Trott's inside edge
short and Cook is quickly on the pull (not like that - he's a married man) to crash a boundary through square on the leg side
length ball on off, pushed back down the pitch
tight line, gets forward and pushes short of cover
length ball and dabbed into the off side
short and wide, Trott shuffles across and swipes a cut shot ... straight to point on the bounce
pitched up and driven towards midwicket
length ball outside off, Trott gets forward in lugubrious defence
full and wide of off, driven on the front foot to the cover sweeper
full and around off, gets forward and punched to mid-off
length ball outside off, pushed into the covers
fuller length, driven through a gap to the man at deep cover
length ball outside off, lets this one through
angled across and punched into the off side
fullish length, outside off and driven straight to mid-off

Lord's falls quiet as Cook chases one outside off and nicks off. Cummins has his first international wicket against England (the first of many?) and Australia's bowlers are finally getting the rewards for their disciplined approach
on the pads and nudged through square, good running garners them a couple
length ball, defended outside off
in the corridor outside off, Trott gets forward in defence
off-stump line, good length, tapped into the covers
back of a length, sticks in the pitch a touch and Trott scoops it short of mid-on trying to work the ball square
short and wide of off stump, Trott turns it round the corner for a single to square leg
pitched up outside off, cover drive through the infield for one
good length ball outside off, Bopara gets forward and opens the face for one down to third man
defended on the front foot outside off
searching for that fuller length, clipped through the covers
fierce bouncer, well-directed from Cummins, hits Bopara on the helmet and neck as he turns away
good length ball on the stumps, Bopara gets forward well in defence
tossed up on middle, tickled to the man at midwicket
flighted but drifting down leg, Trott misses out with an attempted sweep - but it was a wide
tossed up and punched past midwicket and they put pressure on mid-on to successfully scramble one
full and pushed into the covers
tossed up outside off, Bopara opens the face and steers to short third man
bit of spin, outside off and played to cover
tossed up and driven to mid-on for one
back of a length and worked to midwicket pressing forward
full, angling in on off stump but Bopara flicks the wrists and times the ball like a Rolex back past the bowler
length ball, pushed through covers
touch full, driven through extra-cover on the front foot
length ball, played into the off side
Trott steps away and Cummins spies him, sending down a slower ball wide of off and the batsman is marooned, can't connect
tossed up outside off, pushed to the man at extra-cover
shorter length, bit of grip and Bopara cuts fine - possibly via a thick edge - for a couple to third man
short again, goes back and cuts hard through point to the man on the rope
full and flighted, Trott skips forward and pokes Neil Mulligan right in the eye lofts Doherty straight back down the ground for four
length ball outside off, flatter delivery, tapped into the off side
full and on leg stump, swept behind square
would have been a run-out! Dropped into the off side and they race for a single, Cummins collected in his follow through, turned and threw at the non-striker's end which would have had Trott short
played into the leg side
beaten! Lovely delivery, full outside off stump and draws Bopara into a drive
whipped into the leg side from outside off, mid-on moves to his right to field
and one of them is in action as Trott defends a back-of-a-length delivery
loses his line this time, attempted slower ball which doesn't come out right and is dragged very wide
played late by Trott as he guides it fine of the first gully down to third man
sweeps a very full delivery out to deep square
touch quicker, angling in towards middle and leg, defended to the off side
down the pitch and drilled through the off side, but he was nearly done in the flight as Doherty tossed it fuller and wider as he saw Bopara charge but the batsman held his nerve
popped in the air towards mid-on...right where one of the catches was previously when the quicks bowled at Bopara earlier
pushed into the off side
pushed off the back foot into the covers
gone! Strikes first ball with a lovely delivery. Squared up Bopara on off stump and the edge flies comfortably to Michael Clarke at slip who is rewarded for still attacking
off the mark straight away as he drives off the back foot to deep cover
back of a length, defended with soft hands to gully
uses his feet to McKay then drives him over cover to the man sweeping on the boundary
pushed wider outside off and left alone
closer to off stump but Morgan again opts not to play
tossed up on off stump, driven past a diving cover down to long-off
places this square backward of point
punched back towards the bowler who dives in his followthrough
defended off the back foot to the leg side
drives off a thick outside edge to short third man
dragged down shorter and wider, Trott cuts out to the man in the deep...don't suspect Australia will mind Trott keeping the strike
pushed square into the off side
goes across his crease and works it through midwicket out to the sweeper
drives and misses outside off, wasn't that full and he was aiming on the up
on the back foot, opens the face to find the gap
a slower ball which is dragged down a touch short and Trott pulls to deep square
latches onto some width with a front-foot cut which he doesn't time that well and it allows Lee to tidy up from deep cover
nice stuff from Doherty now, draws Trott forward and he pushes to the off side
half an appeal as Trott squeezes this into the off side
full on leg side, beautifully whipped away through midwicket...David Hussey makes an athletic dive on the boundary and pulls off a stunning piece of fielding to prevent the boundary. Brilliant effort
stays round the wicket, worked off middle out to deep midwicket
lovely bowling, beats Trott with one that turns quite sharply. Australia go for two appeals (stumping and catch) and Clarke then reviews for the caught behind. Hot Spot doesn't show an edge
driven down to long-off
back of a length and turned to deep square
comes across outside off and defends back to the bowler
a full delivery which is nicely driven through the off side
takes a straight delivery through midwicket with a tuck off his pads
outside off and left alone
comes down the pitch and outside leg to give himself some room and drives through the off side...placed well enough for a brace
round the wicket, worked from well outside off through midwicket and placed nicely wide of long-on
goes for the cut and misses
connects this time having jumped extravagantly around the crease...gets a single to deep point
defended to the off side
driven out to cover
pushed off the back foot down to long off
back of a length, worked from outside off to midwicket
picks out the gap at midwicket
aggression from Trott, again steps to leg to open up the off side and drills his shot out to the cover sweeper
outside off and left alone
on off stump, leans forward and defends to the off side
driven off the back foot and picks out cover
starts full outside and driven to deep cover
back of a length on off stump, defended to the covers
fuller on middle and off, worked down to mid-on
beaten for pace as he goes for a cut...perhaps wasn't as wide as Morgan thought
flicked in the air through midwicket but it's just a single
drives square on the off side and well fielded by point...excellent over from Cummins
nicely played, taken from outside off stump with a turn of the wrists. It beats mid-on and a laboured McKay can't catch it
pulls the length back a little and pushed firmly to cover
cut in the air through gully and reaches third man in a flash
a full toss outside off stump takes Trott by surprise but he ends up playing it quite well down to third man...as though he didn't pick up that delivery
defended back towards the bowler
ooh, he nearly chops this into the stumps but the bottom edges scoots past Wade to fine leg
another occasion when Trott gives himself room by coming down outside leg stump but can only slice this to deep cover
now Morgan uses his feet too, Cummins responds by dragging the length back and it's cut to third man
dropped was driven firmly back to the bowler but Cummins couldn't hold on
very wide and Trott finally latches onto one with timing and placement as he dispatches it away from deep cover
short of a length, Trott hangs on the back foot and opens the face
big blow! Morgan breaks free by launching a full delivery high straight down the ground and it comfortably clears the boundary
guided down to third man
full and wide, driven in the air over backward point with an open face and more excellent work on the boundary, this time by Cummins, to save the boundary as he flicks it back to his team-mate
pushed square through point
driven off a thick outside edge and it races fine of third man...another useful boundary, some momentum building
angled backward of point and good running brings two to take him to another half-century, this one off 65 balls
sweetly driven through the off side, the sweeper is square and can't cut off the second...12 off the over, to go with 13 off the previous one
pushed into the off side
opens the face with soft hands into the off side but point is in quickly
full outside off and driven out to cover
full outside leg stump and he doesn't get away with it
worked into the leg side, Watson chases himself and dives but can't prevent the single
down the pitch and driven out to the cover sweeper
cut through backward point and these two have run well together
tossed up on leg stump and bowled him! Trott simply missed with an attempted glance through the on side, almost yorking himself as the ball dipped and slipped under the bat to break the wicket
full and on the stumps, studied forward defensive
flighted around off, pushed to extra-cover
tight line, full and straight, driven back to the bowler
touch shorter, Kieswetter goes back and slashes hard , Smith leaps to his left at extra-cover to make a terrific stop and limit them to one
tossed up and across, worked from in front of off through midwicket
touch short, pushed across as Morgan steps out and angles the ball through point for one
length ball outside, coming back a touch, Kieswetter offers no stroke
touch short of a good length, angled in towards the stumps, dabbed into the on side
good length, just outside off, Kieswetter advances and attempts to mow the ball down the ground ... but fails to get ball on bat
shorter length, stays back and defends
pitched up outside off and driven square to the cover sweeper
tossed up on leg, nurdled through midwicket
gives it some air, outside off and Morgan goes down on one knee, doesn't quite connect with the slog-sweep and they get one to deep midwicket
full and one the stumps, straightening a touch, chipped down the ground
length ball, sliding across, goes back and late cuts
full and flighted on the stumps, Kieswetter drills a shot at extra-cover
length ball, cut behind point
pitched up outside odd, Morgan narrows the gap and slams a lusty drive between mid-off and extra-cover for four, fierce stuff
on the stumps and worked to mid-on this time
back of a length, dropped into the off side for one
full and wide, dribbled back down the ground to long-off
slower ball outside off, patted through the covers
full and tickled into the off side for another single
short and shovelled wristily over square leg, that fair flew out of the middle, dying half a yard in front of the rope

bumper again and this time Morgan trampolines it towards third man with the open face of the bat, Wade makes very good ground getting across but can't quite pull off what would have been a stunning catch
slower ball from Cummins, fiddled off the hips into the leg side - and that's a nifty fifty for Morgan, at more than a run a ball
length outside off, driven through the covers
slow bouncer this time, Morgan swivels and guides it round the corner to long leg
another slower delivery, Kieswetter waits on it and dabs wide of short third man, who pulls it in but not before they get one
full and straight, punched through the leg side with a flick of the wrists
takes the pace off it, little bit short and wide but Morgan's flashing blade only finds the man at point
pitched up outside off, Morgan manufactures a drive the infield, out to wide long-on, and they scamper a couple
pitched up outside off and drilled down the ground
slower ball, out the back off the hand, completely befuddles Kieswetter, who misses with a pulled and the ball bounces over the stumps
another slower one, this time clubbed into a gap in front of deep midwicket, good running brings a couple
full and straight, Morgan can't quite dig it out and Lee fields
pitched up wide of the stumps, chopped through cover-point to the man in the deep
another wide full-bunger from Lee, Kieswetter practically falls over bringing his bat down to squeeze the ball away square on the off side
bouncer but taking the pace off it, Morgan had stepped away and is foxed, no stroke played as the ball loops past
full toss and this time Morgan does connect, bunting a maximum over wide long-on

and he goes again! This one was only fractionally overpitched but Morgan stepped out and swiped Lee back over the rope, the same part of the ground, rather undoing all the bowler's good work in that over
and after more than a few sighters, Kieswetter follows Morgan's example by stepping away and crashing the ball back over the bowler's head
full and straight, dug out towards long-off
length ball on middle and Morgan unleashes again, spearing the ball over the rope on the up out towards deep square leg - this is sixy hitting, all right
full length, skips out and lofts over mid-on, well fielded on the bounce in the deep but they steal two
pitched up wide of off, jams his bat down and it runs towards mid-off, the fielder on the boundary is a bit slow to react and they again hustle for two
overpitched, drilled low along the surface, very fine straight back past the bowler and beats the dive of long-off
pitched up outside off, Kieswetter steps out and across, thinking to slog, changes his mind and deflects the ball short on the off side
pitched up wide of off, dragged back down the pitch for a single to long-off
yorker-length outside off, Kieswetter again looking to free his arms and can only chop into the off side
length ball outside off, slapped through the cover region
round the wicket, full and wide, might have taken the pace off a bit and Morgan misses with a big old yahoo
full and well wide, this time Morgan gets under it, the ball slicing away off the toe of the bat, over gully and skipping to the boundary
full toss, whacked back at Watson and he takes a nasty blow on the fingertips
length ball and Kieswetter turns inventor, going down on one knee to flip the ball over his head for four down to long leg
pitched up outside off, drilled through the covers
another full toss, hoicked out towards deep midwicket, who runs around and fields on the bounce
pitched up, angled across, chopped down to long-on
length ball, Kieswetter hits on the up but it goes straight up, long-off comes scampering in from the boundary and takes a well-judged diving catch

inn2.comm: length around off stump and Watson forward to block
almost identically delivered and identically played
ran down to third man and the chase is underway
blocked going back and across off stump
full down leg side
slightly straighter and tucked through square leg
too straight to the right-hander now and worked through square leg
good length on the off stump, blocked back up the wicket
back foot punch through extra cover, fine stroke, just hauled back by Cook at the boundary
blocked on the front foot around off stump
little bit of width and chopped down to third man
length and Warner went to play to leg and got done for pace, getting struck on the thigh pad
much fuller and draws Warner into the drive, he plays and misses
length and played down to third man on the front foot, opening the face
just outside off and tucked to point
fine delivery, leaving Watson from a good length and beating his defensive push
back of a length now and tucked to midwicket
driven without foot movement and another play and miss
this is closer to him and he drops it to cover
angled in and striking the pad
length and left alone outside off
angled in again, Watson goes to whip it away and misses, a strangled lbw appeal
forward to block
big bumper and ignored, wide? Apparently not
dropped in front of cover, Bopara comes in as they take a single and fails to gather so they get home with ease
pulled off only a length really out to the man in the deep on the leg side
length around off stump and blocked back to Anderson
a touch too straight but only a single via midwicket
length and Watson stands still and tries to angle to third man but finds gully
very full and squeezed through square leg for one
length played just wide enough of mid on for a sharp single
full on off stump, driven on the walk to mid off
pushed to cover, Bopara again...misses again when a run out was on, that was miles away
marvellous stroke down the ground for four, Watson is so good in taking a huge stride and then thumping the ball straight, that was a joy to watch

cry for caught behind as Watson looked to back-cut, given not out and England, who were convinced, refer this, there's a noise...and a mark on Hot Spot, this is going to be out and indeed up goes the finger. Watson stood still and tried to angle the ball away and got a thin nick through. England knew straight away, Aleem Dar perhaps couldn't hear the nick because of the wind but DRS again shows its worth
back of a length and blocked back up the wicket
angled in and blocked back up the wicket again
length outside off and this time Warner is leaving
Warner gets a long way across and gets struck on the pad, large appeal from behind the bat, nothing from the bowler, probably too high. pitched just outside too
length and blocked around off stump
a hint of width and carved to third man
length and left alone outside off
slightly short and pulled to the wide midwicket fence
slightly short again and a short-arm pull through midwicket, that will make Warner feel better
too straight and tucked behind square on the leg side
back of a length and cut to cover point
taken from the top of the bounce and smashed past cover, thumping stroke, a little bit of width is all Warner needs
pulled down to long leg and they scramble back for two
another smashed four through the off side
starts back of a length and gets tucked into midwicket
tucked through square leg this time
off stump and blocked back up the wicket
leg side wide
full and left outside off
length and dropped in front of mid on
taken from only just back of a length outside off and heaved over mid on with a pull, didn't really seem to get hold of it either but it sails for a one bounce four, great shot
length outside off and left
pulled to midwicket
length and left again outside off
length and tighter on the off stump now, ran back to the bowler
pulled out to deep square leg
short and flicked at and missed
short ball and hooked away, not in complete control and it was more top edge than middle but didn't carry to fine leg
another short ball and this one is dispatches much more effectively as Warner pulls it backward of square
full on middle and leg, defended towards mid-on
pulls again, this time in front of square and goes straight to Bopara in the deep
outside off, defended to the off side back towards the bowler
opens the face and guides comfortably down to third man
full and worked down to long-on
nicely flight outside off and it's very sedately driven out to deep cover
down to long-on
grips a little and takes a thick outside edge towards short third man
quicker and shorter, Warner onto the back foot and punches to deep cover
worked into the leg side...tidy start from Swann
good start, full on middle and off, Warner defends from the crease
hint of movement back into Warner as he plays to the leg side
stays very straight to Warner and this time he's worked square on the leg side
short of a length, Bailey deep in his crease and flicks it between deep square and long leg
full on off stump, defended towards mid-on
up at Bailey's toes and it's flicked firmly to mid-on which means no chance of a single
dragged down short, cut away firmly but well fielded by Cook at cover
defended from middle stump into the off side
nice bowling, tossed up enticingly and gets a thick outside edge as he drives
goes back and is taken on the pads by a straighter ball (or one that doesn't turn) but it's going well down leg
full and pushed back to Swann...lovely contest brewing
goes back and works this into midwicket so he'll keep the strike
full and thumping powerfully towards mid-off, it pitches just short so makes it quite a tricky stop for Trott
that's big, dropped in short by Broad and Warner's eyes light up as he pulls it over the deep midwicket boundary
back fuller on off stump, defended square into the off side
driven with an open face and but Bopara is in the way at backward point
that could have been nasty...Bopara nearly gets one in the face which bounces in the footmarks of the other wickets
good line to finish with, on off stump and defended back to Broad
pushed into the off side
comes forward and opens the face to find the gap out to deep cover
worked with the spin to square leg, good work from Anderson
full outside off, driven firmly square through the off side
defended off the back foot
flicked along the ground to midwicket
hint of width first up, driven away square and there's a fumble at backward point by Morgan
shapes back into Bailey who plays it late to third man
short of a length, whipped away off the stumps to deep square
opens the face and sends this fine of backward point...comfortably milking Bopara's first over
good work by Bell at midwicket, Warner turned it off the stumps and was keen for the single before having hurry back
takes the pad down the leg side, it rebounds off Kieswetter's gloves towards short fine-leg
back of a length, punched firmly off the back foot to point
playing away from his body, gets an edge but pretty well controlled and beats third man
fuller on off stump, pushed square on the off side
opens the face and pushes through the covers to the sweeper and that's his fifty from 57 balls
that's hammered, just a hint of width from Broad and it's cut powerful square through the off side
responds with a short ball that Bailey doesn't play very well. Takes his eye off the ball as he pulls but it lobs safely through square leg
short of a length, worked off the back foot through midwicket
tight! Pushed into the off side and Warner set off straight away but the throw goes to Bailey's end and strikes him on the back of the leg
aims for the gap in the leg side but gets it too straight to mid-on
wrong line, on leg stump and flicked backward of square...Australia picking up boundaries to keep themselves on track
dropped in short and Bailey cracks away the pull but straight to Bell at midwicket
that will make him feel better! Bailey chops into his stumps. Was too close to guide down to third man and takes a bottom edge into the wood work.
bouncer over and wide of leg stump...too wide for Aleem Dar's liking
outside off, guided down to third man to bring Michael Clarke onto strike
big appeal! Clarke shoulders arms and it flicks the pad as it heads over middle and leg. Blimey that was close. Trusted the bounce
good line, on off stump and Clarke defends to the off side
full at Clarke, which is good early in his innings, and played down to long-on
outside off and a more comfortable leave this time
full on off stump, punched firmly back to the bowler. A good, testing over.
short and pulled into the ground, he rode it well, the ball scudding to the square-leg rope

edged and that's a fantastic snag behind the stumps! Anderson pitched it up, having pushed Warner back, enticed him to drive and a thick edge flew towards first slip (which was vacant), meaning Kieswetter had to launch himself horizontally to grasp the ball. Warner, the danger man, is gone ... Is that a game changer?
length ball, bit of width and cut through point to get Hussey off the mark straight away
overpitched outside off, Clarke drives elegantly down the ground for his first runs too
length delivery, steps out and leaves
drifts on to the pads and clipped fine, Bresnan gives chase but can't quite cut it off
length ball outside off, Hussey stays back and offers no stroke
touch short, defended towards point on the back foot
bouncer, pulled in front of square, didn't get fully on top of it but it landed safe before being pulled in around deep midwicket
back of a good length, knocked to extra-cover on the back foot
length ball, played on the front foot towards mid-off
effort ball from Broad, touch of away swing, Hussey leaves
length ball, on the stumps, nudged into the leg side
touch short, steered down to third man
back of a length, Clarke comes forward and defends to cover
full and tailing in, driven hard past extra-cover, Cook gallops across from mid-off and just about pulls it in
length ball in the corridor, dabbed towards point, they think about one but Clarke elects against it
on the pads, clipped into the leg side
signs of menace again, back of a length, Clarke dangles his bat at it and is beaten outside off
darting in towards off, worked through midwicket off a good length
touch short, played back down the pitch from the crease
short of a length, straightens on off, Hussey prods tentatively as the ball fizzes past the edge and over the stumps
fuller, tucked off the legs towards mid-on
wild delivery, veering away down the leg side as Finn loses control slightly
pitched up outside off, classical cover drive but fielded comfortably
pitched up on the stumps, driven into the on side
bit of width and cut through point off a good length
full and straight, pushed back to the bowler
length delivery, played towards cover
banged in, angling back towards the top of off, Clarke defends into the off side
touch short, on the body and worked square on the leg side
full pitched and ducking back in late in the day, Clarke drives and gets an inside edge on to his front pad, the ball deflecting away and they grab one, despite an attempt at the stumps
good length outside off, Hussey goes back and leaves
short, pushed towards mid-on, this could be tight but Cook misses with his throw at the non-striker's end
pushed into the off side on the back foot
fullish length, on the stumps, solid forward defensive
back of a length, rising up at the batsman, who goes back and across to block
length ball, goes back and cuts fine, possibly a thick edge, but there's no slip and the ball skedaddles away for four
length ball on off stump, pushed into the off side
bit of width, stays back and cuts hard, straight to point
pushed through on a good length outside off stump, no stroke
back of a length, rolls his fingers over the ball, pushed defensively towards cover
fuller length, shapes away from the batsman as Hussey tries to cart the ball over the infield, missing everything and bringing a chorus of 'ooohs' from the crowd
tossed up outside off, punched to mid-on
dragged a bit shorter as Clarke leaves his crease, defended on the front foot
flighted on off, steps out and sweeps through square, there's a misfield but the man in the deep covers it
tossed up, comes forward and knocks back down the pitch
flighted on off, worked square on the leg side
full and on the stumps, driven to long-on
back of a length, on the stumps, blocked short on the off side
length ball, angled in towards middle and leg, shovelled to midwicket
tight line, worked towards point from in front of off - another dot
touch short, prodded towards cover where Bopara collects and attempts a back-of-the-hand shy at the striker's end
outside the line of off, coming back a touch, Clarke plays it on the walk to midwicket
sliding down leg, flicks the pad and Kieswetter takes the catch

bumper, Hussey gets in a tangle, the ball hits him on the helmet ... and drops on to the stumps! Strange dismissal, that, Hussey mistimed his pull completely, was hit on the shoudler, then the helmet, the ball finally plopping on to the wicket
defended in front of off stump
pitched up a tad more, played towards point
back of a length, angling in, defended on the back foot
touch short, pitches and holds its line, Smith plays away from his body and the ball dies before reaching Anderson at second slip, who deflects it past Cook at first
short of a length outside off, chopped behind point for a couple
full and Clarke mishits his drive straight back at Bresnan, who drops a dolly! The ball came off the toe of the bat, flew fairly tamely into Brezzie Lad's bread basket ... but he shells it
drifts down leg and this is flicked behind square for a galling/restorative four
bit of width, swings hard and a thick outside edge flies down to third man
short of a length, Smith pulls into the ground on the leg side
chopped towards mid-on, another tight call is successful, though Smith is hit on the chin byt the throw - he's all right
length ball outside off, pushed square on the off side
on the stumps, worked into the leg side
short of a length, dragged down through point
Smith has a big roundhouse swing at a bouncer, which fairly cuts him in half
full and outside off, driven to cover
touch short, angling down leg, turned off the pads into a gap in front of midwicket
jaffer from Finn, back of a length, rising and holding its line ... too good even for Clarke
length ball, tailing in towards middle and leg, nudged to midwicket
touch short outside off, chopped towards point
length, veering down leg, Clarke wanders a long way across and misses with a glance ... Bresnan appeals for the wicket, Clarke wants a wide; neither gets
short and wide, dabbed through point for a single to the sweeper

length ball, in the corridor and Smith fences weakly at it, nicking through to the keeper! That won't convince the doubters, pushing away from his body, perhaps trying to guide the ball to third man ... but failing
on the legs, flicked off the hips for one behind square
off stump and blocked back up the wicket
pushed out through cover from a length
played awkwardly, a little leading edge back towards Swann
big stride and turned with the spin through midwicket
down the wicket gets struck on the pad, appeal for lbw, there's a conference and no referral, rightly so I think
another step down and a push to cover
back of a length and cut to point for a crowd catch
full and driven down to long off
full, outside off and left alone
left again outside off stump
square driven to point who saves well
played forward to cover, they refuse the second on the misfield, good call
down the track and driving to extra cover who parries and they take a run
swept out to deep backward square leg
fiddled to a vacant square leg area
step away and a cut to cover
flatter ball moved through midwicket but only a single again
down the track but just blocked to cover
ooo thin edge to fine third man for four, fortunate but four nevertheless, the type of fortune Australia need
straight delivery nearly slips past the drive which goes to long on for a single
back foot push to mid on from a length around off stump
square drive out to deep cover
good looking drive down to long off
pulled to deep square leg
swept hard and placed very well, went very square and gets four between the two deep men, good shot
down the track, not to the wicket and almost gets beaten past the outside edge, nudges it to the 45 in the end
length ball turned into midwicket
heaved down the ground, nowhere near the pitch of the ball, dragged towards and short of long on, fortunate there Wade
turned very fine and a diving save saves a run, jolly good work from Anderson
taken from off stump out to deep square leg
full and dug out through midwicket
pulled to deep midwicket
full and flicked out into the leg side wide of deep midwicket
better on off stump and blocked back to the bowler
cut hard through point, a wild return from Swann but does enough to save the single
Clarke came down the wicket but Anderson dropped it in a touch short forcing Clarke to adjust and just block to cover
stepped back to a full ball and pushed through point, dangerous
swept aerially and fielded well on the square boundary
down the track but fired in and just blocked to cover
went for this, down the pitch and the kitchen sink is chucked at this, no idea where it was and it falls at Wade's feet, he scrambles back into his ground
tried to come down again, a little bit of turn and Wade just blocks once more
another step away and cut through point
bang! Picked up off a length into the Mound stand, amazing strike, that was big
driven to mid off
length and nudged through cover, they try for two but not on
leading edge down to long off, so weakly did it travel that they come back for two
turned to midwicket
length, off the pad to backwards square leg
slightly short and cut in front of square for four, great shot
blocked back up the wicket
shot! Massive strike into the Tavern stand, picked up from outside off and timed superbly into the crowd
swept hard out to deep square leg

played into the leg side, oh and there's a huge mix up and Wade is run out! Clarke wanted the run, Wade did not but eventually had to go to save his skipper and was easily run out at the non-striker's end, disaster for Australia
turned through square leg
length and pushed to midwicket
slower ball and a leg side wide
back of a length and chipped over midwicket, long on goes round
stepped across the stumps and turned around the corner, no-one at backward square and that's four more
full ball strikes the pad, a huge appeal, surely going down, given not out but they review it, I thought it was going down, hitting in line with leg stump but indeed, going a mile down
back of a length and taken behind square leg again, two this time

got him this time! A similar delivery to earlier in the over but this is much straight and up goes the finger! Bang in front this is, he swings across it and caught plumb in front, game over now is it?
forward onto off stump and blocked
short ball and Lee ducks, it comes off a top edge and flies over the keeper, the periscope Bumble's called it, left his bat up when he ducked and got a top edge for four!
pushed into midwicket
fine back of a length nip-awayer that McKay gets nowhere near
push from middle and leg wide of mid on
another fine delivery slides past the outside edge as Lee just plodded forward
back of a length, tried to be turned to midwicket, comes off pad and bat to cover
fuller and McKay pushes at it and misses
taken off leg stump out to deep square leg
middle and leg, ran back up the wicket
four over midwicket, a clean strike, one bounce into the grandstand
and now a slower ball wide
much better, not length and allowing Lee to swing his arms, back of a length and he misses with a cut on off stump

down the pitch, straight up and caught by Kieswetter. McKay went for a leg side heave to a back of a length ball that he tried to step down the track to but it just went up and the keeper went to his left to take it with both hands easily
edged cut to third man
length and just ran to point
back of a length and a good shot over short midwicket with a short arm lift and gets it wide of deep midwicket to the rope
beauty, wobbles away off the seam as Cummins just pushed at it into the off side

gone! It looked stone dead, missed a full ball that beat the inside edge, he refers it but this is just out and indeed Hawk Eye confirms as such, that was a ridiculous referral! Right in front on the back pad, if that ain't out, nowt is
pushed to midwicket and they take a couple as the boundary fielders can't get in quickly enough
step away and hammered over extra cover, a lovely strike, smashed to the rope, nearly went all the way, fine shot
Lee steps away, Bresnan follows him and it's, not a wide! Eh!? Must have hit the pad, it was jolly well taken by Kieswetter too
slapped down to long on
pushed at outside off and missed
full toss, ran into the covers and they take a single
back of a length and an thin edge put down by the keeper, tough tough chance
swept off off stump to the 45
ran out through point on a length
fired in and it comes off the a very fine bat and runs away for four past the 45
length and pushed down the ground to long on
blocked on off stump
back of a length, tucked to backward square leg and that should win the game with Douherty on strike
slapped down the ground to long off
a heave towards the leg side goes straight through Steve Finn on the 45, they take three out to the long leg boundary, Finn does well to save second time around
wide outside off and that's a wide
off stump and blocked into cover
outside off, slapped off an inside edge just wide of the bowler
Broad follows Lee's shuffle to leg and gets it through his legs
steps to leg, gets hit on the body, they charge a run, Finn can't hit the bowler's end stump so they take a run
length ball drilled down the ground
inside edge behind square on the leg side to a length ball
length ball, a heave and a miss and England have all but won
slapped into the off side the come back for two
another huge swing and a miss
